BFN 

  [Text] Between 8 March and 10 April, an extensive outbreak 
of diarrhea occurred in Ban Hong La-eng, Ban Uthai, Ban Toumlan, 
Ban Chengsoun, and Ban Meung in Toumlan District, Saravane 
Province. A total of 188 people were afflicted with the 
disease; seven died. Bountong, head of the Toumlan District 
Public Health Service, said that to prevent the epidemic from 
spreading to other areas, the district administration sent 
medical officials to provide urgent medical treatment and 
vaccinations for the people. At the same time, the people have 
been informed of preventative measures and the three hygienic 
principles so that the epidemics will gradually die out. 

